#: src/rust-2021/index.md:9
msgid "Release version"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2021/index.md:9
msgid "1.56.0 (anticipated)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2021/index.md:11
msgid ""
"The Rust 2021 Edition is currently slated for release in Rust 1.56.0. Rust "
"1.56.0 will then be in beta for six weeks, after which it is released as "
"stable on October 21st."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2021/index.md:15
msgid ""
"However, note that Rust is a project run by volunteers. We prioritize the "
"personal well-being of everyone working on Rust over any deadlines and "
"expectations we might have set. This could mean delaying the edition a "
"version if necessary, or dropping a feature that turns out to be too "
"difficult or stressful to finish in time."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2021/index.md:21
msgid ""
"That said, we are on schedule and many of the difficult problems are already "
"tackled, thanks to all the people contributing to Rust 2021! 💛"
msgstr ""
